{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012mAqcvAafNEty4qsNGhQt9","type":"tool_result","content":"# Issue Summary: Leave-API Backend Service Implementation\n\n## Issue Title\n**\"Implement leave-api backend service #1\"**\n\n## Working Directory\n```\n/Users/kajendran/.asdlc/repos/default/kaj-test-17/leave-api\n```\n\n## Core Responsibilities\nThe service must handle employee leave management on port 9090, including request validation, balance calculations using business day logic, manager approval workflows, and status tracking with timestamp records.\n\n## Technical Stack\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Framework:** net/http or lightweight router (gorilla/mux or chi)\n- **Storage:** In-memory with sync.RWMutex thread safety\n- **Container:** Multi-stage Docker build (golang:1.21 → alpine:latest)\n\n## Key Data Structures\n- **Employee:** id, name, managerId, leaveBalances (map[string]float64)\n- **LeaveRequest:** id, employeeId, managerId, leaveType, startDate, endDate, reason, status, managerComments, submittedAt, reviewedAt\n\n## Sample Data Requirements\n- 5 employees with 2 managers\n- Initial balances: annual (20), sick (10), personal (5)\n\n## API Endpoints (OpenAPI 3.0.3)\n1. `GET /health` – health check\n2. `POST /api/leave-requests` – submit request (validate overlaps, check balance, deduct optimistically)\n3. `GET /api/leave-requests` – filter by employeeId/managerId/status\n4. `POST /api/leave-requests/{id}/approve` – manager approval (verify authorization)\n5. `POST /api/leave-requests/{id}/reject` – rejection (restore balance)\n6. `GET /api/employees/{id}/balance` – retrieve balance by type\n\n## Business Logic\n- Business day calculation: `(endDate - startDate + 1) × 5/7`\n- Date format: YYYY-MM-DD\n- Enforce overlap prevention and authorization checks\n- Return consistent JSON error structure: `{error: 'message'}`\n\n## Critical Constraints\n- No required environment variables (use hardcoded defaults)\n- Write ALL files within the working directory\n- Do NOT start the server locally\n- Handle edge cases: invalid dates, non-existent IDs, duplicate status changes"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d672ec57-1012-4cef-9ce6-75f46bb8ef99","uuid":"600b1533-e79e-413d-a5d1-08e089b164c0","timestamp":"2026-04-24T09:02:56.682Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":341106,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Issue Summary: Leave-API Backend Service Implementation\n\n## Issue Title\n**\"Implement leave-api backend service #1\"**\n\n## Working Directory\n```\n/Users/kajendran/.asdlc/repos/default/kaj-test-17/leave-api\n```\n\n## Core Responsibilities\nThe service must handle employee leave management on port 9090, including request validation, balance calculations using business day logic, manager approval workflows, and status tracking with timestamp records.\n\n## Technical Stack\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Framework:** net/http or lightweight router (gorilla/mux or chi)\n- **Storage:** In-memory with sync.RWMutex thread safety\n- **Container:** Multi-stage Docker build (golang:1.21 → alpine:latest)\n\n## Key Data Structures\n- **Employee:** id, name, managerId, leaveBalances (map[string]float64)\n- **LeaveRequest:** id, employeeId, managerId, leaveType, startDate, endDate, reason, status, managerComments, submittedAt, reviewedAt\n\n## Sample Data Requirements\n- 5 employees with 2 managers\n- Initial balances: annual (20), sick (10), personal (5)\n\n## API Endpoints (OpenAPI 3.0.3)\n1. `GET /health` – health check\n2. `POST /api/leave-requests` – submit request (validate overlaps, check balance, deduct optimistically)\n3. `GET /api/leave-requests` – filter by employeeId/managerId/status\n4. `POST /api/leave-requests/{id}/approve` – manager approval (verify authorization)\n5. `POST /api/leave-requests/{id}/reject` – rejection (restore balance)\n6. `GET /api/employees/{id}/balance` – retrieve balance by type\n\n## Business Logic\n- Business day calculation: `(endDate - startDate + 1) × 5/7`\n- Date format: YYYY-MM-DD\n- Enforce overlap prevention and authorization checks\n- Return consistent JSON error structure: `{error: 'message'}`\n\n## Critical Constraints\n- No required environment variables (use hardcoded defaults)\n- Write ALL files within the working directory\n- Do NOT start the server locally\n- Handle edge cases: invalid dates, non-existent IDs, duplicate status changes","durationMs":8222,"url":"https://github.com/asdlc-repos/kaj-test-17535/issues/1"}}
